---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="NudgeBit - Gentle Habit Tracker" description="Habit tracker without punishment. Momentum instead of streaks. Rest days built in. Free forever.">
  <div class="pt-24 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
      <a href="/en/apps" class="text-sm text-text-muted hover:text-accent-purple transition-colors">&larr; All apps</a>

      <div class="flex items-center gap-6 mt-8 mb-12">
        <img src="/apps/drift-icon.png" alt="NudgeBit icon" width="128" height="128" class="rounded-[28px] shadow-lg" />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3"><span class="gradient-text">NudgeBit</span></h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-text-muted">Gentle Habit Tracker</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Screenshots -->
      <div class="mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
        <div class="flex gap-4 pb-4" style="min-width: max-content;">
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_1.png" alt="Habit tracker" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_2.png" alt="Journey view" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_3.png" alt="Momentum ring" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_4.png" alt="Onboarding" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_5.png" alt="Share card" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_6.png" alt="Dark mode" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/drift/screenshots/en/screenshot_7.png" alt="Celebration" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          NudgeBit tracks your habits without punishing you for being human. No streak counters. No red X's. No "you broke your chain" notifications. Just a gentle momentum score that rises when you show up — and barely dips when you rest.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Most habit trackers celebrate your 30-day streak with a fire emoji — then reset you to zero when you miss one day. That cycle of guilt is why 80% of people quit within two weeks. NudgeBit replaces streaks with momentum: a rolling window that shows how you're doing THIS week. Miss a day? Your momentum dips from 86% to 71%. Not to zero. Never to zero.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Why NudgeBit Is Different</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Momentum, Not Streaks</strong> — rolling 7-day window. Miss a day? 86% to 71%, not to zero</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Rest Days Are a Feature</strong> — the only habit tracker with a Rest button right next to Done. Tap Rest and your momentum stays the same. No punishment. No drama</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Start With One Habit</strong> — other trackers let you add 15 habits on day one. NudgeBit starts with one. Grow to three only when momentum stays above 70% for 21 days</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Designed to Feel Calm</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Momentum Ring</strong> — beautiful circular indicator that shifts from lavender to gold as you build consistency</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">28-Day Heatmap</strong> — soft dots: green for done, blue for rest, gray for missed. No red. Ever</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Gentle Phrases</strong> — "Every step matters" at 30%, "This is who you are now" at 90%</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Actually Free</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          No subscription. No "3 habits free, pay for more." No ads. No account required. While Streaks costs $5.99, Productive charges $30/year — NudgeBit is free forever. Your data stays on your device, synced through iCloud.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Coming to App Store</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted">NudgeBit is preparing for release. Free for iOS.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted mb-3">All data on device. iCloud sync is optional. No tracking, no analytics, no server.</p>
        <a href="/apps/drift/privacy" class="text-sm text-accent-purple hover:underline">Privacy Policy &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="text-sm text-text-muted">
        <p>Questions or feedback: <a href="mailto:magic4e@gmail.com" class="text-accent-purple hover:underline">magic4e@gmail.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
